post_text: The 5th grade students took their first math assessment of the school term on Friday. The students have been preparing and studying over the last 2 weeks. Mr. Williamson was in the class and offered the students an incentive for doing their best on the assessment by having a drawing for a Dairy Queen gift card. In order to have their names placed in the bucket, students had to make at 85 or higher. Eight students met that goal, and Aiden Long‚Äôs name was drawn from the bucket. Thank you Mr. Williamson for motivating and encouraging the students to work hard.

post_text: Yesterday our high school students attended the Energy Expo in Cairo. Students learned about various jobs in the energy industry and how those jobs provide electricity to everyone.
